"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-nandos-respond-to-tatjana-gold-paris-2024-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 63, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15, \"end\": 18, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"score\": 0.8521931288634391, \"rank\": 0.1501055007881431, \"text\": \"Sky\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbNando's with a classic response to Tatjana's gold at the Paris 2024 Olympics  These guys never miss.\", \"from\": 65, \"to\": 304, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 107, \"end\": 110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"score\": 0.8521931288634391, \"rank\": 0.1501055007881431, \"text\": \"Sky\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Popular fast food chain Nando's are always sharp and succinct with their responses to current events.\", \"from\": 306, \"to\": 407, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They are on the Tatjana Smith bandwagon after the South African claimed gold at the Paris 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 408, \"to\": 512, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rightly so.\", \"from\": 513, \"to\": 524, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tatjana Smith had a different surname when she stunned the world in 2020 with gold in the 200m breaststroke final, posting a world record time of 2.18.95.\", \"from\": 526, \"to\": 680, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More of a specialist over that distance, she's claimed gold in the 100m after scooping silver in Tokyo three years ago.\", \"from\": 681, \"to\": 800, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 778, \"end\": 783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.7402934175719125, \"rank\": 0.35081570745585183, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tatjana Smith, previously Schoenmaker when she broke the world record to claim gold in the 200m breaststroke event four years ago in Tokyo, has won gold again.\", \"from\": 802, \"to\": 961, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 935, \"end\": 940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.7402934175719125, \"rank\": 0.35081570745585183, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This time, in the 100m event in Paris.\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 1000, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 994, \"end\": 999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999677129, \"rank\": 3.2473151107013314e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"27-year-old Smith won silver in this event in Japan but wasn't to be denied in Paris, touching the wall first in1.05.28thanks to amassive surge in the final quarter of the race.Worldwide commentators hardly mentioned Smith in the second half of the race but she got the job done by the skin of her teeth.\", \"from\": 1001, \"to\": 1305, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1047, \"end\": 1052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9994123994147461, \"rank\": 0.00029300011830663214, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 1080, \"end\": 1085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999677129, \"rank\": 3.2473151107013314e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"China's Tang Qianting scooped silver and a visibly delighted Mona McSharry, from Ireland, got the bronze.\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1411, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1306, \"end\": 1311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999976086643472, \"rank\": 2.1278476380322122e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1314, \"end\": 1327, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tang_Qianting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tang Qianting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tang_Qianting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tang_Qianting\"}, {\"begin\": 1367, \"end\": 1380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_McSharry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mona McSharry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_McSharry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_McSharry\"}, {\"begin\": 1387, \"end\": 1394, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.5635870688287123, \"rank\": 0.7742900580973527, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"South Africans must have had their hearts in their mouths for a second.\", \"from\": 1413, \"to\": 1484, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As a staff member from The South African said after race when Smith was the red-hot pre-event favourite, \\\"Thank heavens the race was 100m, not 99\\u2026\\\"  If you missed the race, what on earth were you doing?\", \"from\": 1485, \"to\": 1687, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's footage of a stunning event which went South Africa's way.\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1753, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1734, \"end\": 1746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.127867051814726e-13, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Just.\", \"from\": 1754, \"to\": 1759, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"South African sprint sensation Akani Simbine ran a time of 9.93 seconds at Tokyo 2020 in the 100m final.\", \"from\": 1761, \"to\": 1865, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1792, \"end\": 1805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Akani Simbine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That meant he missed a bronze medal by a heartbreaking four-hundredths of a second behind Canada's Andre De Grasse.\", \"from\": 1866, \"to\": 1981, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1956, \"end\": 1962, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.8683655396715345, \"rank\": 0.15151437836956544, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Italy's Lamont Marcell Jacobs was the surprise gold medalist four years ago in a wide-open field that Simbine fancied his chances of winning in the Land of the Rising Sun.\", \"from\": 1982, \"to\": 2153, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1982, \"end\": 1987, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.9637978152832644, \"rank\": 0.037165173600646695, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 1997, \"end\": 2011, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcell_Jacobs\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marcell Jacobs\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcell_Jacobs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marcell_Jacobs\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Four years before that, Simbine finished fifth in the 100m final in Rio De Janeiro; the medalists that night were iconic Jamaican Usain Bolt with gold, USA's Justin Gatlin claiming silver and De Grasse scooping the bronze.\", \"from\": 2154, \"to\": 2376, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2222, \"end\": 2225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999998158273, \"rank\": 1.839482492501137e-10, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2275, \"end\": 2283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.7905738503366699, \"rank\": 0.26490396763557894, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}, {\"begin\": 2306, \"end\": 2309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998546500243, \"rank\": 9.681747985661145e-08, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2312, \"end\": 2325, \"title\": \"http://